<p>
  <span class="nym">Abigail</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Hebrew</span> <i>אֲבִיגַיִל</i> 'her father's joy'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a Biblical wife of King David. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Abigail</i>. Geneva Bible (1560): <i>Abigáil</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The name was popular in the 16th C amongst Dutch, English, and French Protestants.</p>
</div>
  


